    "attributes": {
        "action": "PAYE Income tax over-payments returned automatically",
        "additional_details": "From my experience, it has become clear that a timely refund is almost impossible and trying to get hold of anybody is a nightmare at HMRC and individuals are powerless.  Those on a low income can ill afford the stress of not being able to pay bills, supply children with food or pay the mortgage with this length delay. \r\n\r\nFor example, I contacted and was told \"Too near the end of the tax year, you'll have to wait\".  Now well into the new tax year \"Can't do anything as we don't have a P11D\".",
        "background": "If during the year PAYE tax is deducted incorrectly (e.g. via an incorrect tax code) it can take 6 months to get the money reclaimed, even if the error is highlighted on day one. In an age of digital transactions, this should be re-paid efficiently as many low incomes depend on correct taxes and pay",
